0 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: Beauty, eh?
1 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: It's all looking splendid!
2 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: F looks unlikely to recover Nap. Are you thinking he will be down to one fleet sustained by Mar? Or with your fleets lined up to advance into the Med has he just outlived his usefulness?

3 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: I can consent to you taking norway this turn, though I don't know how many other centers you anticipate gaining. I anticpiate netting 1 w/o you taking norway, and so would net 0 with you taking norway, just FYI for keeping our growth even.
4 GERMANY -> ENGLAND: I'm trying to split Sev/Rum with Turkey, but I'm getting a bad feeling from him. At the same time, I wouldn't think he's at the point where he would actually SH Sev to block me. I think the prudent thing to do is for me to hold off on taking Nwy. Worst case scenario, you end up +1 and I end up even. IMO, that's better than you even and me potentially up 2.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: My allies are growing increasingly frustrated at your lack of progress against England. You have yet to move a fleet above MAO, despite ample opportunities to do so. I would like to consider you my friend and ally, but if you are not with me I will be forced to accept their belief you are allied to England. I doubt I can keep them from considering you fair game any longer.
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I have not moved there because I've been playing defense, defending Brest; perhaps if England had been knocked out of the EC by you, me, or both of us, I'd be further along. I still want Engand dead- BADLY. His presence, as you can see, is a constant threat. And as far as "you'd like to consider me your ally," I let you into my territory- what further proof of loyalty do you need? The board shows that I literally GAVE YOU Burgundy. I did not do so to be chastised, I di so to allow you to better fight in the north while I defended. ~N~ ~N~ And as you said, I got Italy to back off and end that front, so I am fighting here- it's just hard to go on the offensive against England when she's right at my throat. I need Portugal and to get England out of the EC before we go through with your idea, which I do like- I just need to get in postion to do it, which I'm not in right now, as I think you'd agree. ~N~ ~N~ If you can think of a way to get England out of the EC soon without my losing territory or letting him into the area around Spain, by all means, tell me.
2 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Too hard to get England out of the English Channel. Instead, see points 1,3, and 5 above. The best way is to move Brest to EC every turn so as to immobilize his fleet there. If he tries to move EC and NS down, it bounces NC and splits his fleets, and disrupts a convoy line to Spain.
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I see you've support-held Burgundy, as if expecting me to-n take it back? Why would yoiu stay when you said you were borrowing the land, and why would you suspect an ally like me who has already lent said land would attack[1578038]
4 GERMANY -> GERMANY: NOTES
5 GERMANY -> GERMANY: Well, Spring 1903 Shows an Alliance of Russia/England/Italy vs. me :(

0 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Ah, man, that sucks. Misordered the Con convoy. We could have had Sev AND Rum. :) I have no clue what Italy is doing at this point. I told him to head west towards France. I didn't get back to my comp in time to change the unit taking Bul. Agreed that it would have been better to have my fleet on ION. Con or Smy should be open for a fleet build after this. We may need it, depending on what Italy does.

What do you think? Can you turn Italy around? I will try to do the same.
1 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: For Fall, I think you hit Sev with two units, Rum being the mover. I will send one unit in unsupported into Rum in case you get in. That way you get a build worst case, and we both get builds best case and I could use the build to put one more unit on Italy if he doesn't steam west.

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I realize that Turkey and Austria don't really work well together...but good luck with [187712].
1 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I'm not one to just keep silent and allow my fate to be sealed, so more than likely, you will continue to receive messages from me. They aren't necessarily intended to be annoying, but if they are, no skin off my back. :) ~N~ ~N~ I spoke with England...he says you are committed to Russia. I just wonder how long you intend to prop up a lame duck. ~N~ ~N~ Russia will not get a build this year...I'm sure I said that. And he needs to move to Black Sea for either of you to break me. How is it that you will be able to restrain yourself from this sea of purple that lay before you? You could drive a damn truck through there. His forces are split and he's in bad position. ~N~ ~N~ I might also throw in that he's a bad decision maker and a poor ally. :) Okay, that one was a bit out of spite.
2 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: Sooner or later you will have to turn on Russia. France is a growing threat and will soon dominate with England. ~N~ ~N~ I'll bet you are hoping to put me down before he/they can gain enough momentum...you may want to look a few more turns ahead there. France will break Italy at around the same time you break me. Germany will be destroyed and Russia will not be able to hold his northern lines. ~N~ ~N~ So you'll get what? 1 -2 Sc's while the FE alliance will split a few each. And once Italy and I go down, France dominates the Med...you have no fleets.
3 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: I'm building fleets.... I won't be able to keep up with French fleets, but I don't necessarily have to.... he has two naval fronts to protect.

2 ITALY -> FRANCE: Understood. And yeah, I'm really disappointed in England, too.

1 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: so we have some time left... lets try to finalize our plans here. are you ready to hit russia? if you are, you get rumania and put an army in gal this spring, in the fall, I'll be there to help.

i'm fine with you taking rum, sev and mos as well as the turkish centers you plan to split with italy while I get stp, war and nwy. I'd even be willing to give you warsaw in the medium term to even things out as that also gives us both a better stalemate position so we dont threaten each other. what do you think?
2 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I'm glad to hear your continued enthusiastic for the CPA. I really feel that it's the best course of action for us three to be successful in this game.

Yes, I think it would be a good time to move on Russia. I won't ask for the specifics of the maneuvers, but I hope to see your troops rolling in at Russia in the mid-term.

Long term, regarding the division of lands, all of that sounds quite reasonable. We can sort out the details once we get there and have a clearer view of the situation. Of course, ensuring an equitable and defensible position for both is the primary goal.

How are things going in the west? Are relations with France getting better since the foray into Burgundy?
3 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: let me say this... France and I are talking through things constructively... but i want to tell you a secret. I only tell you this because you and I have committed to this CPA triangle and to show you that I trust you. France has told me you asked him about my move, and he asked me permission to tell you that he's pissed at me. so he will tell you we are at war, and my answer to you will be we are at 'war'. we are working out a deal to make it look like we continue to remain at war while nothing changes hands... I tell you this in the strictest of confidence and please please do not share this intel with russia or italy.

you can tell them I've said 'we are discussing paths to peace but there is little trust' or something like that... but what is important is that France also wants me to attack Russia and working out a deal with France will be relatively important in moving on Russia.

if you manage to take rumania and take gal in the spring, I will do my part in the north.
4 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Thanks for keeping me the loop about that. I have and will certainly keep that in the strictest confidence. By the way, all I asked France was what he thought about it. I hadn't spoke with him in a while, and felt like opening by asking about the elephant in the room.

I got an interesting piece of press from Russia. He said he thought the move into Burgundy may have been prearranged. I didn't ask about that with him, he just brought that up as a random remark during conversation.
5 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: tell france that russia told u that, that will piss off france. intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Well Italy did not build a fleet and Austria destroyed both of his. Looks like the forecast is for fine weather and smooth sailing in the med.
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Do you think we could make the black sea a DMZ now please?
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Yes, I had to lie to IT a lot and promised him to make an army and attack you. Understandably, he's quite pissed. AUS, I guess, is trying to save himself and focusing on his home centers.

Yes, I'll move out of the BS and will also try to take GRE next turn. I assume you're going for BUD and you should have no problem taking it?

There's some chance that IT and AUS will come together now, hope GER doesn't decide to help them, though you two seem to have a solid alliance. We should be ok though, that is quite a good start for a Jug actually :)
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: You have managed the Italian negotiations superbly :-)
If Austria is a good diplomat he will try very hard to get Italy onside - I would say those two helping each other is on the cards.
With regards to Germany, I am hoping that those western powers keep fighting each other just a bit longer - naturally they are going to get wise in the near future, but I am hoping that by then this steamroller will have serious momentum, and thus far all signs indicate that it will.
4 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I must take Bud this turn. Rum can support Galicia, but if Vie supports Bud the move will fail. Do you think you think you could support me from Serb. I realize you would probably like to support [501477] to Greece, I think you have the necessary firepower already. And if you you are unlucky and fail to take it in Spring, you can force the issue in Autumn. Thus end of the year +2 Russia/Turkey, -2 Austria.
After that we just push straight through the South and Center - nothing will be able to stop us. You will naval supremacy in Med, and our combined armies will prevail on land.
I don't expect my North to expand further at this stage, but it does mean that we outflank our rivals.
5 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: typo above... I realize you would probably like to support &Bul to Greece (with Serb)
But as I say we need to make sure we take 2 Scs this turn, and the only way to guarantee that is if we take Bud in spring and Greece in Autumn.
If I have missed something or if you a better plan, I am, of course, open to other suggestions.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I suppose I should have guessed I was due for a stab by the silence after my last message.
Still I was a little surprised. I would have thought the path of least resistance would have meant that you would work for me a little while longer yet. Also this stab wasn't exactly the decisive fatal blow that one hopes to achieve with a stab. While I can see that you might be able to come out of this with the upper hand it won't necessarily be easy.
I am pragmatic though. If you change your mind let me know. I could have been a great ally for you, and another opportunity for you stab me would have arisen.
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: ... as in the final stab before the win (assuming we hadn't decided to go 17/17)
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Hello. I'm very sorry for not responding earlier. Haven't been able to check the game in more than a day. I also need to apologize for the stab and, before I start explaining why I did it and what I would like to offer now, I'd like to say I'm very keen on trying to keep the alliance with you.

So, first, some explanations on why I attacked you after you being a great ally, even letting me in the BS.
1. I am very much scared of you and Italy splitting me once Austria is gone.
2. I had promised you to move out of BS, which effectively made this spring turn the perfect moment for you to attack me. Taking BUD from GAL and moving in BS behind me would have placed you in a perfect position and I already have Italy quite willing to fight me. I have three fleets after all.
3. I guess I was tempted to find a way to keep some positional advantage over you for the time-being, as the risk of going to war now seemed less scary than the risk of you going to war with me if I start looking like an easy target.
4. Once I decided to go for the stab and thinking about what will happen after, I realized there's a good chance I may be able to offer a reasonable deal to you. Plus, everyone else being convinced we're at war is not such a bad thing.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: So, here's what I can suggest, I'm open to other ideas also.
1. I will move RUM-BUD with SER support and BS will hold.
2. If you keep SEV at place, so that you can't build fleets there, I will continue against Italy, if you help me you can take BUD and VIE and can take TRI?

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Okay, so what do we do this turn? I probably need to protect Trieste, but I could leave it open on the chance they decide to try something sneakier. You should be able to get Marseilles this turn if Germany agrees and you're willing to give up Wmed for a turn. The Balkans will be the real problem here
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Germany is in agreement, and this means we can hopefully advance against France - once Marseilles falls, there will be one more fleet to face Turkey, and I suppose I'll be able to press forward towards Iberia.

Well, on moves... There is certainly a variety of options to explore. We could try to guess where Turkey is attacking from and hit the supporting units, you could consider using Vienna to cover Trieste and supporting Ser-rum. I think we should also expect your fleet to be disbanded - either because you'll lose a SC or because it will be forced to disband even if you keep Serbia/conquer Rumania.

In reality, a new army would greatly help you, so I don't think that would be necessarily bad. We could also consider having your fleet hit Aeg to minimize the risk of Turkey dislodging Ionian - if we can hold it for one more season, a new fleet build can greatly boost our position.
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Okay, I've locked in something along those lines. This ain't going well for us, but we have a chance if we can coordinate everything very well.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: So, what do you expect me to do? Overall, my plan is to conquer Marseilles, build a new unit to fight Turkey. Take advantage of the French disband, see if I can conquer Spain, and build a new unit to fight Turkey, repeat with Portugal, and then pray.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Well, just so you know I'm support holding Greece, even if I think it unlikely to make a difference.

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> ITALY: I suspect you are worried, about my placement of a fleet in Smyrna. Rest assured, the fleet is not aimed toward you per se. Allow me to explain myself:

To be a successful Turkish power I cannot completely lie down in the Mediterranean, I need to place some fleets there for my own protection.

Secondly, the eyes of of every sultan are turned towards Gibraltar. I truly liked your move to Munich. It immediately launched you into a powerful diplomatic position, if I can cross the straits early on, I will gain significant diplomatic influence with England and France.

Third, I would not have been able to expand far enough intoo Austria this turn to move another land unit out of Asia minor. While my position may be enviable for its natural defensiveness, the counter edge is the increased difficulty of the offense. I like to play offense and this was the only offensive move I could truly make.

And lastly, you are still of some use to me as a friend

All of this to say, I am asking your permission for passage towards Western Mediterranean. Please do not give my fleet reason to end its Western voyage early.

-Sully
1 ITALY -> TURKEY: I will grant you permission to sail through the [996250]. If we make this work - it will be a sign to all nations that great differences can be overcome in the pursuit of common ends.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Of course, any falsehood will be treated accordingly.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I can't believe how France is just giving the game to Germany.... This is just bonkers. Can I ask you to move Sev to Armenia, so we can remove Turkey, or do you think he could be useful?
1 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I must admit I've had to suspend disbelief over your moves too, so six of one....

I'd love to move into behind Turkey, and take him out, but am (understandably, I think) still a little nervous about Austria. If we can get a more complete plan, I'd be happy to do so.
2 ITALY -> RUSSIA: Austria and I are talking frantically with France to try and get him to stop assisting Germany to the win.

That, frankly, was the outcome I hadn't expected. I had expected F and G to be fighting, whilst, honestly, Austria and I eventually removed you two, leading to a joint alliance against one of the two bigger powers, leading to a 3 way draw with A/I and one of F and G.,

The stab by Germany, yet with France assisting, has left me gobsmacked - I never expected that, especially as, in league play, he gets no points for a second place to a win.

Austria and I now have no choice - we have to work with everyone left - you, me and him, to try and achieve a draw. France will, I think, work with us as he has said he will switch sides as long as he can guarantee particpating in a draw that leaves him surviving.

I think a blockade is workable here. Moscow and Sev support each other, Ukraine supports Warsaw, Gal supports Warsaw, Rum supports Gal, Vienna and Tyrolia support each other, Venice works with Rome, whilst Adriatic, Ionian, Mars, MAO, Tunis fleets can set up a blockade in the west.

Smyrna, Sev and Bul can take down the remains of Turkey, leading to an extra unit for Italy and Russia to assist in stalemate duties.

France, Austria, Russia and Italy work for a five way draw with Germany - eminently achievable, as the stalemate line is already there in most places.

I'm copying this to all parties - France, Austria and Russia (to who this message was originally written).

I seriously think this will work. Otherwise, we just limply hand the win to Germany, and concede defeat in the League season after just two games, as a win in the last two games is unlikely...

0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: What's going on with the army build instead of the fleet build? Your position isn't looking too hot all of a sudden.
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I've got two fronts to deal with. I know you would like me to think of England and England alone, but I also have to get a little aggressive with Italy.
2 GERMANY -> FRANCE: That's cool. I just feel like another fleet could have protected you against Italy even better. I figured Burgundy was going to Gascony, while a fleet in Brest could have supported MAO.
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I can't do both fronts without easing England's mind, even if it's just slightly. He's anxious enough that he can't concentrate totally on Scandinavia, which should be important for you. At the same time, I need him to drop his guard just a little.

4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Ok, that makes sense to me. I can rationalize the army build from a diplomatic, long-game standpoint. If I've got the opportunity, I'll build a fleet so we have enough for a future invasion. Though, if things progress like they are now, we might fall into a Western Triple out of necessity.
5 FRANCE -> GERMANY: They say a Western Triple always gives way to something else - usually after an English stab. I think patience is worth something in the early going here.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, I guess he retreated nowhere. I'll support your fleet to London in the spring if you allow me to take Edinburg in the fall. Sound agreeable?
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Edi is yours. For that matter, so is Lon. I need to go fend off Italy.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Grab Edi now. I'll follow behind Wales so if he gets to Lon, I can use Wales to support you in. Let's finish him this year.
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Pic is moving off to work down to Gas for defense.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: No problem. I'd love to get you a build someplace. You'll need the added fleet to prevent Italy from taking the MAO. I'm moving to Edi this season. See you again in 7 hours or so. Next year, I'll give you at least one build, even if it's at one of my centers so that you can get that fleet.

I see Italy moving a fleet to Naf and WES so that he can use the fleet in Gol to cut support at Spa and use his other 2 fleets to force his way into the MAO in the spring.

If that happens, then I'll have to use my fleets to support you until you can get your own in place.

If you get this message before th end of the phase, I recommend moving Burgundy to Gascony and Picardy to Burgundy. That way, you can get another unit in place in the south to support holds.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: Though slightly surprised, I appreciate your compliments!, even if I find them undeserved. I admire your tenacity - a characteristic I share - and wonder to what bets you're referring.

I also appreciate the disband, and shall honour what I proposed. We need to find the ideal set of moves, but I'll get there in a moment. I'd just like to point out that Turkey, who has been comprehensibly lobbying for an attack on Austria, has just remarked on how unstoppable England and Germany, as allies, are bond to become sooner rather than later. While I said nothing, it does calm me to know my concerns (namely, regarding Germany) are well founded, meaning my choices are, apparently, wise.

Now, as for moves, we're in a tight spot. There are many possibilities, and even supporting you into Burgundy (Gas-bur and Spa-gas) is not completely sure to give you Paris. You could consider asking Russia to launch an attack on Munich, in order to tie German units there, though I'd advise caution regarding my allegiance :)

But our main (perhaps only?) advantage is that, as far as I know, Germany is unaware of my stance. Meaning I can know precisely what moves Germany intends to order, and perhaps steer them in our favour.

I assume England will support Bel-pic, so that Brest falls to them in the Autumn. If Germany is not concerned about covering Paris, I can suggest Bur-gas, Mars S Gol-spa. Seems feasible. The plan is good in that, even if you do not attack Marseilles or resist in Gas and sneak into Paris, they can surely support Pic-bre, offsetting that loss, while you're also weakened in Iberia, meaning Germany may fall for it.

On the other hand, instead of supporting Gol-spa, I can support Spa-gas. This means you'll not only sneak into Paris, but now your two armies will be able to support hold Brest, while only one of these supports can be cut by Germany. You keep your 3 Scs, Germany goes down one and our position is, albeit mildly, improved!

I'll suggest these moves to Germany, but I'm waiting for your ideas before committing to it.
1 ITALY -> ITALY: Ok, it seems to be all set regarding the convoy.

I had an idea, though. Do you think you can possibly persuade Russia to enter flawed orders?

I don't know how it would be best to pull that off, but our position would be even better if Serbia-rumania actually worked.
2 ITALY -> FRANCE: Ok, a small setback. It appears Germany is actually inclined to cover Paris. I haven't looked at it closely enough, and I'm quite tired, but it seems to me our best option, in light of that, is for you to order Gas-bur and Spa-gas. With your army in Burgundy, there are many interesting options. You can outguess Germany on Brest, reclaim Paris, or even join forces with Russia and conquer Munich!

Still, I've replied sceptically, so we may yet see a change of mind on Germany's part. Besides, I'm still waiting for your thoughts!
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: France...?

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: So, do you think Ank will support Con to Smy, or that Ank and Black Sea will support hold at Con? If Ank supports Con to Smy, Aeg should support hold at Smy while Smy supports Bul to Con and Greece supports Serb to Bul, that will get you Con. I'm sure Arm will support hold at Sev, so if Black Sea and Ank support hold at Con, we likely won't get Con regardless, so I'll input those orders unless you suggest otherwise.
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: First of all, sorry for not getting back to you sooner. Life has been hectic as usual and I've been seriously neglecting the game.

That is an interesting set of messages. It's not too surprising to hear that from Germany, as he is a crafty player and would do what he can diplomatically to improve his chance of potential solo, or at least strengthen his position to insure his share of the draw. However, England also echoing that concern and specifically predicting that Germany would be sending that message is an interesting play. England is quite a skilled and intelligent player as well. His ability to diplomatically deflect the 3v1 situation that he was facing is quite a testament to that, and I certainly think he is aware that a strong CPA has formed. With a strong CPA, he knows he can't make it to the draw, but at the same time, he can't just come out and attack Germany and risk further galvanizing our alliance. His best play would be to create internal tension within our alliance to try to rip us apart, while working with Germany for the time being to possibly strengthen his position to be included in the draw.

I have no grand delusions of a solo in this game. It's quite clear that you, Germany, and England are far too experienced let something like that happen. I believe the best play for me and for our CPA is to work toward the 3-way draw. Getting England out of the picture may be tricky, but I think we will be able to accomplish that. I concur with your observation that we have the failsafe of establishing the corner stalemate position (provided that we eventually clean Turkey and Russia out of that area) in order to prevent any possible ambitions of an EG alliance. However, I think that Germany is also aware that any long-term partnership with England is not in his best interests, as none of us want to see our 3-way draw turn into a 4-way draw, and hopefully he doesn't have any ambitions to leverage a partnership with England to set up for a solo attempt, which I think would only make a great mess of things.

By the way, England and Germany did not mention anything to me about watching out for an Italian solo. Actually, England has been trying to pit me against Germany, telling me that he thinks that Germany may try to solo and that we need to unite to squash that threat. I imagine that England is also talking to Germany trying to pit him against you, in order to negotiate his way into the draw possibly with you cut out of the picture. England needs to expand into France to strengthen his position and working with Germany is the only way to accomplish that.

Ok, that's enough paranoia and speculation for now. I think the less paranoid interpretation of the situation strongly reinforces the notion that Germany is committed to the CPA. Before the spring moves, he was facing potential hostility from E, F and R, but he was able to diplomatically influence England into making moves that went quite well for Germany. He moved into Sweden and can take Norway this fall as well. If he follows through with that, it'll be devastating blow on England and remove any worries about England and Germany.
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Ok, as for moves: Yes, I agree that your suggestion would probably be best. It's a safe set of orders that guarantees Smy and a Turkish disband and makes a safe play on Con if Turkey does something stupid. However, it's probably most likely that Turkey will just hold Con with support from Bla and Ank.
Just to reiterate:
Gre S Ser -> Bul
Smy S Bul -> Con
Aeg S Smy

By the way, I offered Turkey support into Sev last turn and I actually issued that order. I'll offer the same thing to him again (but I won't actually give the order this time). It would be ideal for us if used Ank to cut Arm and attacked Sev with Bla, but I know it's quite a long shot.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: All sounds perfect, great analysiss, I'm excited we are so in tune to each other's way of thinking. I too pefer to see this CPA to the end, so will try to check my paranoia. I've got along well with Germany, and even though England is trying to pull me on his side, I will just play nice long enough to get Germany and me into position to take him down. All's looking good and I've submitted those orders we discussed. Good luck with Russia and the north!
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Germany is saying that the other powers are telling him that you and I have been trying to undermine him diplomatically. He seems quite annoyed, but it seems that he'll may likely give us the benefit of the doubt. I'm trying to reassure him.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: He sent me a major paranoid message too. My bet is England is making some guesses and pushing his buttons. I sent Germany a long message telling him I'm 100% behind the CPA, which I am, I'm just 200% behind our alliance, so if he freaks out and does something crazy then we have the option to pull in someone else, I just hope he can keep it together.

0 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: Greetings, i have (perhaps unwisely at 28 points ) taken on England
i offer you an alliance against Russia & France
i will support army Ruhr to Holland with fleet North sea
& attack french fleet Eng Ch with fleet Wales & risk London.

you can either take the offer or not
if you do i ask that if you do not move army Kiel to Ruhr,
which is possibly the thing to do,
you should consider strongly moving fleet Denmark to Baltic sea
and army Kiel to Denmark,
so as to defend Kiel & Berlin from a Russian fleet in the Baltic,
& give you the opportunity to attack Sweden
1 ENGLAND -> GERMANY: i have put in provisional orders
fleet Wales to Eng Ch
& fleet North sea to support
if you get back to me with a message would you please
clearly confirm go with those orders,
or if you are game and play the army Kiel to Denmark, fleet to Baltic,
& want to move army Holland to Belgium then clearly ask for a change
in the support order from fleet North sea

i sent france a message
that i would support a german counter attack with fleet North sea,
had made you the support offer
& that he should perhaps delay convoying an army to England one move''

i did not mention my fleet wales, nor any other specific attack details
i have to make him use fleet Eng ch as a support for Belgium
by telling him about fleet North sea
& have him gamble on me moving my fleet Wales to London
to keep Belgium
i have not had a reply from France.
i will do as we agree & support your army Holland to Belgium with fleet North sea
gamble with London and move fleet Wales to Eng ch
good luck
Italy & Austria will fight Russia in the balkans & Turkey

0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: well done on the [74197] of greece. ~N~ Where do we go from here? ~N~ ~N~ I was thinking a combination of R/T/F vs G/I ~N~ ~N~ Our DMZ is working fairly well, and I think it should stay in place. We need to discuss the Vie/Tri/Alb problem. I can always offer support, from Budapest if it is needed. ~N~ K
1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Sounds good - G/I is in the way of both of us, but France isn't in a position to attack Italy right now (and doesn't look to be going after Germany either, unless he suddenly moves Belgium to Holland, Picardy to Belgium, Burgandy to Ruhr, and Marseilles to Burgandy and gets you to hit Berlin to break support of Munich for him). Suggesting to France that he could pick up two centers this turn might get him to bite, and F Mar built at the end of the year would help against Italy. ~N~ ~N~ I think Italy will hold both Trieste and Vienna this turn, so if you support Serbia into Trieste, I'm sure Venice will be holding it so Italy will keep it - is there any way you can move around to occupy Bohemia, Galicia, and Budapest? This would put you in a good position to take Vienna if I hit Trieste with Serbia. I am considering moving Greece to Albania, and Aegean to Greece, forcing Albania to retreat to Adriatic. I'm also considering moving Smyrna out to Eastern Med and hopefully getting into Ionian soon. Not sure if it's worth risking losing Greece and getting it back again next turn, though, since Italy might anticipate and use Ionian to bounce me out of Eastern Med.
2 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: France has been hectoring me since the begining of this game to attack germany, now that I have made the first moves I am pretty sure that he'll jump on the chance to prosper from the fall of germany. I will suggest to him however that he also considers moving A Bur - Ruh to place pressure on Munich. ~N~ ~N~ I to am pretty sure Italy will place support on both Vie & Tri this season. I was already considering moving a Gal - Sil, but am thinking seriously about amending this to Gal - Boh. regarding Serbia I would be grateful if you would consider supporting my army budapest - hold. this is just in case Germany's A Vie decides to support A Tri - Bud.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I can hold Budapest. I think you're probably right, although I also wouldn't be surprised if Trieste hits Serbia in order to break support of Greece. But Aegean will support Greece, so Serbia will be free to support the hold.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: So what about this.. Den can tap KIE while Nth supports Bel to Hol. Bur can cover Bel and I'll move Par to Bur.

Por will head to MAO and then to W. Med and if I get dislodged from Den, I'll just fall back to Sweden.

I'm debating also about whether to bounce Barents in Stp.
1 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Also.. Germany has gotten over his 'pissed' state and is now trying to see if I would still work with him. I'm tempted to play along and see how he feels being 'duped'.

Have you heard anything from him?
2 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: I like your plan, I was going to suggest it myself; however I had reservations about suggesting that North Sea remain in North Sea. I mean, What English player wants a French fleet in the North Sea?

Regarding St Pete, I can't really offer any advice. It's a crap shoot. The Germany player is no dummy but he might be getting desperate. Even after taking Moscow he is set to lose one unit and maybe two if he loses Holland. If he can save Holland and trick you into moving our of Norway, he is set up pretty well for next year. for taking St Pete and maybe even Norway after you retreat from St Pete to Norway.

I have not heard anything from Germany to cause me to think he will react one way or the other. I suspect he knows that I will not agree to cooperate with him in any capacity after his stab.
3 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: I am not sure how to dupe Germany at this time. He is not really in a position to help you against me nor is he any position to help you against anybody else. Any cooperation with Germany would have to be based upon promissory notes delivered in the future, a risky business and I wonder if Germany would even believe it. You are of course, in a position to work against me (Brest/Spain) but that helps you, not him and that is my risk to take, not his.

Actually, as I think this through, I am in the best position for you to dupe, not Germany.

[685932]!
4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: So..... MAR >GOL, BUR>BEL, BEL>HOL, NS spt BEL>HOL Those are my moves. Use me or abuse me.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: Well with a potential juggernaugh on the way that would just be silly. (PS I only got to log on briefly.)
1 ITALY -> FRANCE: What is the best case scenairio in an attack against me? Turkey joins up and in turn gets really strong? Don't you want to divide and conquer?

You have an excellent opportunity to surprise Germany this turn. I can help by letting piedmont into Tyrolia. Thoughts?
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: I'm not opposed to the idea...but I definitely need to flush it out better than that. The best case I can see is that I can be in position to take one SC by the end of the year if I'm lucky. What am I missing? Or more appropriately, how do you suggest we work this into a long term strategy?
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: The long term strategy depends on your end game goals. Geographically, F/I/R is one of the easiest three way set ups on the board.

Its true that attacking Germany is cumbersome. I would say just about as equally cumbersome as attacking me. But the difference is you don't have to worry about the juggernaught nearly as much if you don't attack me. A strong Turkey is especially bad as he will be impossible to dislodge if he grows further.

Look at the map. Do you have a massive stab opportunity right now? No. You don't. But that means Germany won't be expecting it. But far more importantly, is there any chance of you losing anything to Germany? No. There isn't. You will slowly grind him down into nothing, especially once those fleets start circling around England. (I would suggest asking Russia to support you into North Sea). If someone helps you against Germany it will go faster. If no one does you will still win. You have the upperhand, and the geopolitical balance tipping isnt as bad as if you squished me.

0 RUSSIA -> ITALY: That isn't good enough, I'm afraid. You can't count on my continued support, on the contrary, you can count on my hostility.

Turkey is a dead man walking. you can kill him either way with very little by way of concerted effort. Austria is your only threat, and one who you can take on head on at the moment. Why not do so?
1 ITALY -> RUSSIA: Because I fear that if I attack Austria, then I lose my only ally, to be faced by an angry Turkey who I've attacked, coupled with a relatively angry Russia...
2 RUSSIA -> ITALY: But at the same time a rational Russia, who realises that he himself has a pretty pissed off Turkey.

My intention in this game is simply to try to get a share in the draw. An alliance with Italy therefore makes alot of sense, because we are next to the stalemate, whilst Turkey is a long way away and so getting the stalemate will be difficult, or require supporting a half dead Italy anyway.

Remember, all I want is what I was saying from the start. I still want it now, because anger has no part in my diplomacy.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: Just for the record, I apologize if my press upset or angered you. My only intention was to assure you that I recognized you were planning to move against me, and that I saw through your attempted deceit. I had no intention of actually angering you over the issue, and I myself am far from angered by your plans or diplomacy.
1 FRANCE -> ITALY: No I was not angry. I appreciate you writing me now.

I didnt mean to lie to you and I never planned to move against you though. I dont like setting up an NAP or DMZ and then breaking it, especially not so early in the game. Its just stupid to do that!

Suddenly a triple was forming-you are right-and in order to not get run over by E and G I reluctantly agreed. It was last minute and the computer did do that data lock-but those are not really excuses. Suddenly I had to break our DMZ in order to be in the triple and I hated doing it and it was last minute, but you had every right to be upset. If it were me in your shoes, I would have been even more upset than you were.
2 ITALY -> FRANCE: I broke a DMZ the very first turn, so I got you beat there, lol.

I actually don't usually ask for Dmz's, especially since it's possible I may need to move to a place in order to attack someone ELSE... and end up angering another neighbor... ugh.

Anyway, it's all good.

I STILL think you'd be better served attacking England than Turkey and I though :P. Imagine if you did, Turkey would have no reason to cooperate with me. I wouldn't be able to go after you, because I'd have to handle a Turkish stab.

The only reason there's a solid I/T alliance is because there's a F/E alliance. While England is tied down in Germany is your best chance to catch her off guard. You won't get a better chance than this.
3 FRANCE -> ITALY: very interesting. I will definitely consdier it

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: Now that France is committed against England, have you considered switching sides? Could be an excellent powerplay that leaves you with two countries off balance rather than a really strong France secure in his corner.
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: Nah, RUS and TUR have just allied for good and you hit AUS at the same time - this is a huge risk for the whole East to collapse. I will wait for at least a year to see how things develop there before making any changes.
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: If you are worried about the juggernaught, I think you can trust that I have a handle on the situation.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: :) I don't really think you do. I wish you did, but this is not what I hear from the others. Depending on how AUS reacts you might be in a real trouble. Don't count on RUS and TUR to start fighting any time soon.

In any case, to the main point of the discussion, I really don't need a war with FRA now and think it will be a bad decision for me.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: You see, the thing is. I didn't tell either of them that I was stabbing. So unless you have heard something from them recently, things have changed.

As for France, he is about to get a lot of growth pretty quickly. I want you to fight him because obviously that means he won't fight me. But I actually think its far more likely for him to fight you given his northern orientation.
5 GERMANY -> ITALY: But that's exactly my point - they agreed on an alliance at the same time you stabbed - how did you come to the conclusion that this is good for you? If you and AUS keep fighting you're both dead, this is what I see.

I know FRA will expand and maybe take 2 centers. I will take care to cover myself as much as possible, this is why I made an army and not a fleet.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Time to make plans. Are you ready to roll? :-)
How do you want to play this? We really want to see Trieste and Vienna fall this turn. After that you should be able to gobble up the Italian Scs fairly quickly I hope.
From there we should divide the map in half and aim for 17/17.
But I am really hoping that you don't get wet feet and attack me. We are positioned for the most perfect jug. I promise to be a true ally and I want to make sure that we both grow equally. I am little ahead in Scs at the moment but I am also fighting on more fronts than you - and I think after this turn you will catch up quite quickly.
Let me know what you would like to do.
1 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Actually when I say Trieste and Vienna fall this turn - I mean this year. They can't both fall in spring.
2 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Hi, yes, I'm sticking with you for sure. We're so mixed up with Italy that I don't think we can even try to turn it around. One of us has to die for the other to live...

I will move BS to CON and SER will again attack TRI. You should be able to take VIE this way.

I may get ION into the AEG, which will make things a bit easier for TRI next turn.
3 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Despite encouragement from a certain south-central European power (who shall remain nameless) I would like to assure you that I will NOT be moving to Bla this turn. I am really hoping that Bla will finally become a DMZ, freeing us both up for the Western push.
I am going to put my faith in you Turkey. I think my faith will be well placed because the mutual benefit is clear. The alternative would result in a messy quagmire that will hold us both back.
So I am counting on you attacking Tri this turn. I'll take vie in Spring and you Tri in autumn. I am excited! :-)
I think our plan is quite straight forward. But let me know if there is anything you else on your mind or any other thoughts you want to share. Or if you change your plans - message me so we can figure something else out. But this does seem to be the best move this turn.
4 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: No change of plans on my side. I'm hitting Tri and moving out of the BS. You've been a very solid ally so far and I have no desire to risk it. Italy is talking to me a lot also... but it simply makes no sense to change sides.
5 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Great! Fingers crossed this all goes well.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: So, as I look at it, I expect England to support Bel-pic. This leaves us a couple of options.

Supporting you into Gas has the downside of allowing France to retreat into Paris. If you were to move another army to Burgundy, that would be no problem, but I can't see how you would do that without leaving yourself vulnerable to Russia. Do you think England would be willing to possibly support your fleet into Brest?

If we either order Bur-gas, Mars S Bur-gas and Gol-spa, or Mars S Gol-spa and Bur-gas cuts support and France sneaks into Paris, France's only unit near Brest will be the army in Paris, which your army will be able to hit and ensure Pic-bre supported by the English fleet works. If you consider appropriate, I can already message England on that, urging the English fleet to support you in, instead of the other way around.

Though in theory a setback, France will end up losing Spain and Brest, and conquering Paris, thus disbanding. You'll keep your SC count, and Paris will be easily retaken against a 2 SC France the next year. Given that Portugal will likely fall next year as well, I'll be able to afford handing you Marseilles as well, while I assume England will eventually want Brest.

What are your thoughts on this?
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: I am moving paris to protect the sc & hopefully support eng to brest. Hope this is ok - i want to be a good ally
2 ITALY -> ITALY: Ok, it seems to be all set regarding the convoy.

I had an idea, though. Do you think you can possibly persuade Russia to enter flawed orders?

I don't know how it would be best to pull that off, but our position would be even better if Serbia-rumania actually worked.
3 ITALY -> GERMANY: Well, this is ok, but it appears to be slightly ineffective. But bear in mind that you'll need to move Bel-pic for the attack on Belgium to succeed, or else the single army in Gascony can effectively defend Brest.

But, just to understand your relationship with England, you don't think England would support you into Brest if, given France sneaking into Paris, it made more sense?

I can support hold Bulgaria if you'd like, or support Constantinople into Bulgaria. I have been true to my word thus far, and will continue to be. The only way I see us building trust going forward is to continue to have our actions reflect our words.

4 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: That'd be great, thanks.
5 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I'm going to be supporting Austria into Trieste this turn, any chance you could support Greece into Serbia? Greece will probably get destroyed this turn if he cant get out of there.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> ITALY: Phew.. you hadn't submitted orders by the time I went to bed, I was worried we miss our chance!

I'm set to support Tyrolia into Munich (though I'm worried about a break, so I'll ask Russia if he can support you in as well to guarantee success). Let me know if plans have changed, since I see Austria might be a threat at this point.

Thanks again for leaving the Med, of course!
1 FRANCE -> ITALY: Please confirm you'll be moving to Munich... if I can't get confirmation I'll have Russia support Burgundy in instead, because we really need to take Munich quickly before Germany has the chance to build another unit and defend..
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: Let's see.. Russia is asking instead that you move on Trieste (I assume he plans to help you in somehow by cutting support?), and that he supports me into Munich.
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: I would indeed like to move to Mun. I would like to find a scenario that works for Russia and I--I know you and he are talking--but it's difficult to see how I last long after Austria's demise. What do you think?
4 FRANCE -> ITALY: Regretfully, I've decided to take Russian support into Munich. After the betrayal from England, I've been trying to convince myself that I can hold to our agreement, but I don't think I feel comfortable losing a unit at this point.

That said, I think Russia may be our best possibility for an allegiance (though with the chaos of this game so far, it's hard to imagine any long-term alliances just yet..). You should seriously consider a move against Italy, both because it would probably gain you a build or two, and because it would likely convince Russia that he has enough to support to move against Austria/Turkey himself.
5 ITALY -> FRANCE: No problem. I will go ahead and move East and, as you have suggested, I will look to secure an alliance with Russia as well.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Hi Russia, sorry about not getting back to you sooner. I didn't have much time to devote to the game at the end of last week with work getting hectic. With the weekend here, I finally have some time to sit down and get to some proper diploming.

Thanks for the support hold on Bulgaria as Turkey certainly looked threatening with those three units around Bul. Interesting moves from him at the end of the day. Perhaps, he actually does intend to just let me have his centers, but likely he just figured I wouldn't try that risky move.

Italy wanted me to give him Greece last turn, but I "mis-ordered" Gre->Ion instead of Gre->Aeg to keep it from him. I think I've convinced him that it was an honest mistake, but waiving the build seems to have really sealed the ruse; and even without that build, I can still force Venice.

Tough break with England taking Sweden. That was certainly came down to guesswork. However, covering Norway and putting Germany into the North Sea was the better move, as you can just force back Sweden this turn.

I think we're in good shape moving forward. What are your thoughts?
1 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: Yeah, the Sweden thing was unfortunate but hopefully not a long term hiccup. I'm interested to see what Germany and France do this turn; I've heard that the move to Burgundy was prearranged but I doubt Germany will back off...doesn't seem like his style, really.

With regards to Italy, you have a great shot at Venice this year, hopefully he won't convoy to Apulia. I recommended that he go to Syria, which would be nice for you. As for Turkey, we'll see this year whether he is serious about letting you into his centers. I assume he'll bounce himself in Ankara and cover Con with Aeg but who knows. What are your plans with your one fleet?
2 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: I think I'll just use the fleet to cover Bul as Turkey is liable to try anything at this point.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Well, Russia was pretty adamant about Denmark. I did tell him I'd support him in if he joined me against Germany, so I must hold up my end of the bargain.

Anyway, to be clear, EC and Pic are supporting Bur to Bel while MAO supports hold at Spain. Italy has told me he will take Tyrr to Ion, to help Austria, so that's a step in the right direction, but I'll believe it when I see it, I still fear West Med taking North Africa while Tyrr slides into West Med, though we can cross that bridge when we get to it.
1 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Well, I have talked with Russia and he seems commited to work with us against Germany. I mentioned the possibility of leaving Den to you as a build will help the fight against I/G, but I think he wants to be sure that he will get at least one build this year.
Well, if Italy go that way, we will have some problems, but I think we can deal with that, even losing Spa we can still hold the line with your fleets and my armies.
2 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I hope you are right about Russia, I am a little nervous about him, especially when me makes comments to me about he feels bad for Germany.

Anyway, I'm all for Italy heading east, that's the quickest way for Germany to fall and for us to get some pressure on Austria and get the heat off of you to push into Italy. I imagine Italy running around like a chicken with its head cut off, if he makes a move east, we push at him, then he'll need to come back and ultimately not do anything productive at all.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Mmm, I plan to get Italy as soon as possible. Germany is already weakened enough, so I'll leave you to him. I don't know about Italy other than he and Turkey and ganging up on Austra-hungary. I fear Turkey would be the biggest threat to us if he continues to expand like this. ~N~ ~N~ So I'll move against Italy and ease pressure off Austria-hungary, letting him and Russia deal with Turkey. Meanwhile, you can flood down on Germany and Russia, and advance on Austria-hungary and Turkey as I come from the side. ~N~ ~N~ If you plan to convoy, then can I ask you to convoy from the North Sea and not the English Channel? We still have that as a neutral zone, right?
1 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I won't be moving into English Channel without your permission. ~N~ ~N~ Okay, hit Italy hard and I'll go for Russia and then Turkey. Austria won't hold. Please be mindful of the fleet situation with Italy... we'll need Mediterranean fleets eventually.
2 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: And I without yours. ~N~ ~N~ Then it's settled. For some reason, the game only allowed me to build in Paris, so I couldn't get a fleet at all during the fall. Once I get a few more supply centers, my fleets shall be patrolling the Mediterranean.
3 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Yeah... all your home supply centers are filled up. Let's see how it goes, but you may need to get Belgium to build another fleet. I mean, I'd rather not lose the center, but I'll be in trouble too if France is not strong.
4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: I definitely would not want to take that away from you. Don't worry about it for now. I have confidence that I can take away Italy's supply centers in time.

1. Convoy POR back to BRE or GAS - so that you feel a bit safer from me. I am not moving to BUR, but it's a huge risk, so let's sort this out.
2. Try to take the Channel and I'll move a second fleet against ENG - to HOL probably.
3. Depending on how talks with RUS go I should be able to hit NS to cut support there.

I understand where the moves you suggested come from, but MUN-SIL and BEL-RUHR just make no sense as moves, we'll be wasting time.

0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Well, sorry for last turn, but I have problems trusting Italy, now that Austria stab him, he seems to be really interested in working with me.
I think this turn will be really important, so how you feel about starting to kick England out of the continent? If you want I can support Ruhr into Holl while Italy is offering support to me into Bre. I have disbanded Bur, so you don&t have to fear nothing from me.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I could definitely go for that plan - what would you be expecting in return?
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Well, I have been talking with Italy and he suggest that Russia could hit NS and you can support yourself into Holl, while I move Par to Brest with Gas support and Bel to Pic to force the army on Brest to disband.
Do you think this is a reasonable plan, or it&s too much to trust on four countries agreeing on that plan?
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Also, this will open the chance to Hol retreat into Bel, so I will need your support to try to take it back, maybe next year.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I think this could work. It sounds like Russia and Italy are on board so let's give it a go - you and I haven't got much to lose, so if we at least act together, then we can hopefully get on a par with our other allies.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Hello again. Clearly the Russian will not go down without a fight. Could we agree to not attack each other's territories and instead co-operate against the Russian?
1 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I agree not to attack you or move onto your territory. I also volunteer to get out of Tyrolia as soon as I can make Italy either submit to a Ionian DMZ or I own Venice. I'm sure you won't mind either of those results.

As for moving on Russia, I cannot do that yet because that would be my death. He and Italy would tag-team me into oblivion. Currently Russia thinks I'm an honest bloke, and I don't want to waste that sentiment just yet.

I think it would be beneficial if you focus on Russia while I focus on Italy. However, if Turkey helps me against an Italian attack, I would gladly reciprocate him. He doesn't trust me for obvious reasons, but a word from you may help him not be persuaded by Italy. A strong Turkey is in your best interest against Russia, and I'm willing to defend and support Turkey.
2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Thank you. As usual, it's great to work with you. I will naturally have to focus on Russia, and I appreciate your non-aggression in the south. Good luck with your campaigns, and when you can vacate Tyrolia, know that I will respect that demilitarized zone. Thank you for your cooperation and good-natured diplomacy.

Regards,
Germany

0 GERMANY -> ITALY: Yes indeed! Can we keep Gas dmz? In return i will supp you to brest if you get into mao
1 ITALY -> GERMANY: I assume you meant Burgundy? I mean, it seems that our strongest moveset is precisely Spain moving to Gascony, so that we can ensure we triumph against Brest in the Autumn.

More specifically, if we order Por-mao, Spa-gas and Par S Spa-gas, England can bounce Por-mao, but can't stop Spa-gas. In the Autumn, England will be forced to choose between support holding Brest or bouncing Por-mao. Even if England decides to defend Brest, this means Por-mao succeeds and we're absolutely certain to get Brest next Spring.

What do you say? Burgundy, as far as I'm concerned, is definitely to be a DMZ!
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: Meanwhile, I'll see if I can get the new fleet to move West, so that England can't hope to retaliate against you.

The issue regarding the East is a bit more complicated, though. I can stall Turkey in the Sea, but how can we best support Austria? Even if Austria can't be propped up indefinitely, we should delay its collapse as much as possible. Do you think we risk Trieste falling and order Ven-tyr? If Trieste makes it, our position is surely stronger to push Russia back.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: Ok spain to gas. I guess you need me to hold back the russians & turks, so i am a better ally for you than the brits.
4 ITALY -> GERMANY: To be perfectly honest, I think you're an ally without which I can't hope to stay in one piece. I've being doing my best to prop Austria, as I can't hope to withstand them without Austria. If, or rather, when, Austria is further weakened, I can't possibly hope to hold my own against Russia and Turkey by my own (nor, as a matter of fact, can you). To make things worse, Russia does not answer me at all, meaning I can't possibly drive a wedge between them. If one of us goes under the bus, so does the other.

0 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: We can come to an agreement with my units pulling back. Would you care to vacate Sweden to SKA, I can then support you into Norway. Baltic Sea's move to Denmark would also be greatly appreciated.
1 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: Then what? I really don't want me in Nwy and you in Swe. You in Nwy is a different matter, but you in Swe still poses a threat to Den/Bal.

It's also quite possible I could get Nwy on my own this turn if E doesn't cover.
2 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: The only way to get me into Norway is to pass through Sweden. We can figure out the details from there for a switch. It is only one unit, not much of a threat.

You would go out of your way to create another potential threat?
3 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: No, I'd rather defuse a potential threat and focus on France. However, I'm not sure that Swe-ska, Gob-swe is the best way to accomplish that. What do you think of Swe-nor, Gob-swe? I think E is going to stay put in Stp. I would be more comfortable giving up Swe if I were taking Nwy at the same time.
4 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Your moves are your own, I was just trying to offer something undeniably likely to succeed. I still think my suggestions are better for this reason.
